1
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:56,360
Don't go. You'll all die.

2
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:06,480
Have you all
lived in this house for a long time?

3
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,680
Are you alright?

4
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,040
Where is my child?!

5
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:37,600
Or you ordered them to kill me?

6
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,360
Or did you…

7
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,400
kill our child too?

8
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:53,960
Mr. Phum, did you kill our child?

9
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:56,480
Did you kill our child?!

10
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,880
Da, it's me.

11
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:34,320
Na! You scared me to death.
I thought that ghost was after me again.

12
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:38,560
Come on, Da.
Are you still thinking about the ghost?

13
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,080
A ghost really haunted me.

14
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:43,440
Your house is obviously haunted.

15
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:47,760
Da, it wouldn't sound good
if my parents heard you say that.

16
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:51,840
I don't care. I really was haunted.

17
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,240
If you don't believe me,

18
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:56,960
then just go home. I want to rest.

19
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:22,120
Because of that damn ghost,
everyone thinks I'm crazy.

20
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,360
Why doesn't she go haunt somebody else?

21
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,560
Because I can't contact anyone else.

22
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,920
Calm down. Pull yourself together.

23
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:01,160
This is my condo. There's nothing.

24
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:05,120
I'm probably just hearing things.

25
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:59,560
I need your help.

26
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,360
You have to help me!

27
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:06,080
"Illegal coral bombing.
Everyone involved dead, no one survived."

28
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:14,600
ILLEGAL CORAL BOMBING

29
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:16,040
EVERYONE INVOLVED DEAD,

30
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,160
NO ONE SURVIVED

31
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,800
Those useless amateurs.

32
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:23,600
They deserve to die.

33
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:33,360
Looks like I'll have to hire
those people again after all.

34
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:54,000
Oh, going for a run?

35
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,240
Yes, Dad.

36
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,320
Don't go too far, okay?

37
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,640
Okay, Mom.

38
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:08,640
- Here's your coffee.
- Oh, thank you.

39
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:12,440
Are you really
going to build the aquarium?

40
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:15,920
It's my dream.

41
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,960
And now that I've met Mr. Narathon,

42
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:21,200
I know for sure
my dream is going to come true.

43
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:25,320
Alright. That's good.

44
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:28,880
But Mook doesn't seem
to like Mr. Narathon very much.

45
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:33,960
That's a good thing. She's careful
and doesn't trust people easily.

46
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,240
Once they work together more,
they'll naturally get closer.

47
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:41,560
I'm afraid it won't be that simple.

48
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:57,200
Oh. Looking for the boss? He's not here.

49
00:13:58,960 --> 00:13:59,960
Where did he go?

50
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:01,960
Somewhere around here.

51
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:06,640
Well, did you hear about the people
who bombed the coral?

52
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,240
Oh? You haven't gone to see it yet?

53
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:11,160
They already found the bodies.

54
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,320
I'm sorry.

55
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:55,920
Hey. You again?

56
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:59,080
If you don't want to look at dead bodies,
come this way.

57
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:05,880
You can let go now.

58
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,080
Are you afraid of those criminals?

59
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:12,040
Those people were criminals?

60
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:13,120
Yes.

61
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:16,160
They were coral bombers.

62
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:23,560
Karma really caught up with them
in this lifetime.

63
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:28,400
They probably got blown up

64
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:30,880
by their own explosives
while bombing the coral.

65
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,560
Looking at the bodies,

66
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,160
it seems like
they died from something else,

67
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:40,640
not their own bombs.

68
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:42,640
Something else?

69
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,040
What was it?

70
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,840
Hey, they're all dead.

71
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:57,520
At least they got the bodies back.

72
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:01,960
You think the cops are gonna arrest us
for taking those guys out there to die?

73
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:03,280
Why are you being so loud?

74
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,720
Dead men can't talk.

75
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:35,600
Hello.

76
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,600
<i>I have a job for you.</i>

77
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:39,640
What kind of job?

78
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,400
<i>Find Sarai's family treasure.</i>

79
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:48,360
If you succeed, we split it 50-50.

80
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,920
Interested?

81
00:16:57,120 --> 00:17:00,200
That job sounds life-threatening.

82
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:04,280
Then plan it carefully.

83
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,880
I'm sure you won't die.

84
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,200
Are you coming down there with me?

85
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,359
No.

86
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:16,359
I'll pay for everything.

87
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,440
Buy you must lead the team yourself.

88
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:27,560
Then I'll think about it first.

89
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:32,840
If I get caught,
I'm definitely ending up behind bars.

90
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:38,880
Whatever your answer is,
tell me right away. It's urgent.

91
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:56,920
- Pong.
- Hey!

92
00:17:58,440 --> 00:17:59,560
Are you alright?

93
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:07,920
What's wrong, bro?

94
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,360
They finished moving the bodies.
Shall we go?

95
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,400
Yeah, let's go.

96
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,120
Is something wrong?

97
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,440
Nothing. Let's go.

98
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:17,960
No!

99
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,920
Look ahead. Don't turn around!

100
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:25,080
Don't turn around.

101
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:30,040
Don't turn around.

102
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:52,080
Wait.

103
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:56,360
Why won't you answer my question?

104
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,640
You really want to know that badly?

105
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:04,480
Enough to run after me?

106
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:07,640
I hate leaving things unresolved.

107
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,840
If you're going to say something,
say all of it.

108
00:20:11,120 --> 00:20:13,120
I was just talking nonsense.

109
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:16,600
No, you weren't.
I know you know more than that.

110
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:20,840
So how did those criminals really die?

111
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,800
A curse, maybe.

112
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,640
A curse?

113
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:28,280
What kind of curse?

114
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:33,480
Mook.

115
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,280
Hello, Mr. Thon.

116
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:46,360
Hello.

117
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:49,120
Mook, I need to talk to you.

118
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:52,360
Then let's talk at my house.

119
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:55,720
No. I'm never going back to your house.

120
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,360
Then where do you want to talk?

121
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,560
Can we go to your house?

122
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:11,520
Please, Mr. Thon.

123
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:17,440
Alright. Sure.

124
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:20,000
Let's go.

125
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,920
Then wait for me. I'll go home
and change my clothes first.

126
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:25,760
Hurry up.

127
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:29,360
Let's go on ahead, Mr. Thon.

128
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:43,160
Make yourselves comfortable.
I'll leave you two to talk.

129
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,760
Mr. Thon,

130
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,680
I want you to hear this too.

131
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:50,000
Da.

132
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:56,040
I don't want Mr. Thon
thinking I'm crazy or mentally unstable.

133
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:04,400
Please, Mr. Thon. I want your advice too.

134
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:09,640
Da, what exactly is the matter?

135
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,560
What are you trying to say?

136
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:22,080
That female ghost haunting your house

137
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,520
followed me all the way to my condo.

138
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:52,040
I'm scared. She's here.

139
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:54,440
She's here.

140
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:57,600
Scared of what? It's me.

141
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:05,240
You didn't come to the temple for lunch.
I thought you were sick.

142
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:09,760
Kang, give him the food.

143
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:16,600
Eat up, mister.

144
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:19,200
It's all delicious.

145
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:20,600
Okay.

146
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:39,280
Venerable Sir, what happened to him?

147
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:51,840
What I said was true.

148
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:59,080
Tell him I didn't lie.

149
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:01,360
You knew I could see spirits.

150
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:12,560
Da always sees things we can't see.

151
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:19,560
Sixth sense?

152
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:25,760
Mr. Thon, please help me. I'm going crazy.

153
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:28,040
That ghost follows me everywhere.

154
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:30,440
Mr. Thon, I'm scared.

155
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:32,160
I'm really scared.

156
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:38,440
I don't think Mr. Narathon can help you.

157
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:43,720
But I think
I know someone who can help you.

158
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:50,120
She may be in trouble.

159
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:53,760
That's why
she's trying to find someone to help.

160
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:58,920
Do you have a way to help her?

161
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:05,400
Each person bears their own karma.
No one can carry it for someone else.

162
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:09,960
The only thing we can do

163
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:13,360
is pray regularly,

164
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:16,240
make merit,
and dedicate the merit to her spirit.

165
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:20,960
That may help that woman's soul
move on to a better place.

166
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:25,760
But I'm really scared, Venerable Sir.

167
00:25:25,840 --> 00:25:28,440
I don't want that ghost
coming near me again.

168
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:34,080
NO WISDOM WITHOUT REFLECTION

169
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,480
Here. Come here.

170
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:50,320
Keep this with you.

171
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:53,760
That woman's spirit
won't be able to come near you.

172
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:15,320
Hm. Where is Mook going?

173
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:17,200
She hasn't come home yet.

174
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:19,400
Should we drive around to check?

175
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:23,000
She already came
to change her clothes and left.

176
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:25,040
Oh? Where to?

177
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:28,800
She's an adult now.
Just let her live her life.

178
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:31,280
I'm just worried about her.

179
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:33,400
She still hasn't had breakfast.

180
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:35,640
She could have gastritis.

181
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:38,560
She must have eaten at the market.

182
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:42,240
She bought you shrimp porridge
the other day. Remember?

183
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:28,240
Hello, are you the owners of this house?

184
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:31,480
Yes, we are.

185
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:32,760
Do you need anything?

186
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:34,560
My name is Phum.

187
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:36,840
I'm very happy to meet you both.

188
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:41,920
Why would you be happy to meet us?
We've never met each other.

189
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:47,320
Hey, be nice.

190
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:48,840
He doesn't look like a bad person.

191
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:53,160
Not looking bad doesn't always mean
he's not a bad person.

192
00:27:54,120 --> 00:27:54,960
Hey.

193
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:58,320
You're right.
It's hard to trust people these days.

194
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:01,120
But I can guarantee I'm not a bad person.

195
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:06,920
No bad people
would reveal themselves to others.

196
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:10,080
It takes time to see through them.

197
00:28:11,640 --> 00:28:15,280
Hey, why did you say that?

198
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:18,120
It's alright.

199
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:22,000
I like straightforward people.
I'm a straightforward person too.

200
00:28:23,280 --> 00:28:24,760
Then let's get to the point.

201
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:29,080
I'm interested
in the plot of land next to yours.

202
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:31,400
Looks like
we'll need some time to discuss it.

203
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:34,160
I don't think that'll take long.

204
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:37,200
Because I can tell you right now.
I won't sell it.

205
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:39,240
I hope you understand.

206
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,800
Goodbye, Mr. Phum.

207
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,480
Please excuse us.

208
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:05,160
I think you were too rude.

209
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:09,560
Even if we don't want to sell the land,
you could've spoken nicely.

210
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:12,720
You acted like you hated him.

211
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:15,240
I don't like his face,

212
00:29:15,320 --> 00:29:19,840
his personality. I don't like
anything about that Phum Witassanai.

213
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:25,160
Wait, you know him?
Is that how you know his surname?

214
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:30,440
I know him very well. He's a businessman
who only cares about money.

215
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:34,040
Listen. If he comes back,

216
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:37,840
tell him no matter what happens,
I'm never selling that land.

217
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:43,720
After the welcome you just gave him,
I doubt he'll come back.

218
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:46,800
You still don't know him very well.

219
00:29:46,880 --> 00:29:50,760
Anything that can make him money,
he'll never give up on easily.

220
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,640
Why did you go back to my house?

221
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:51,680
What do you want?

222
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:04,360
Kang, you don't
have to clean the house today.

223
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:06,880
Just feed the fish.

224
00:31:12,960 --> 00:31:14,000
Thon,

225
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:18,560
I still haven't spent
all the money you gave me last time.

226
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:22,880
Take it. If there's any left over,

227
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:25,040
save it for emergencies.

228
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,840
- Here.
- Thank you.

229
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:30,440
I'll get going then.

230
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:31,400
Okay.

231
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:39,400
You're really kind, Mr. Thon.

232
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:41,720
Oh, no.

233
00:31:42,320 --> 00:31:46,240
Kang's a good kid. I just ask him
to help clean the house

234
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:49,600
and look after the fish ponds
when I'm away.

235
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:55,080
Are you heading back to Bangkok now?

236
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:58,880
Not yet. I was
going to invite Mr. Thon to lunch first,

237
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:01,880
as thanks for bringing me here.

238
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:07,520
Hey, I think the one who brought you here

239
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:08,960
was me.

240
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:13,800
Same difference.

241
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:17,600
Mr. Thon still came along too.

242
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:20,240
Mr. Thon, let's go eat together.

243
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:24,880
Mr. Thon probably won't go.

244
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:28,360
Sure.

245
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:31,200
Ms. Da was kind enough to invite me.

246
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:34,560
Great!

247
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:37,000
What about you, Mook?

248
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:41,320
You're probably busy, right?
It's fine. I can drop you off first.

249
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:42,240
Okay?

250
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:46,640
It's fine. I'm coming to eat with you too.

251
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:48,800
I haven't eaten anything
since this morning.

252
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:50,880
Let's go now.

253
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:58,440
- Please.
- Thank you.

254
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:42,400
Are you okay?

255
00:33:50,120 --> 00:33:53,160
I'm okay, sir. You just startled me.

256
00:33:53,680 --> 00:33:57,120
You live here too? Where's Narathon?

257
00:33:58,200 --> 00:33:59,680
- You came to see Thon?
- Yeah.

258
00:34:00,360 --> 00:34:03,160
I saw the house open,
so I walked in, but nobody was here.

259
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:06,760
I left it open myself.

260
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:09,639
I was gonna clean the house
after feeding the fish.

261
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:11,840
Thon went out with his friends.

262
00:34:12,719 --> 00:34:15,000
If you want to wait, please have a seat.

263
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:16,960
I'll get you some water.

264
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:19,440
You're impressive. Hardworking

265
00:34:19,520 --> 00:34:22,360
and well-spoken too. Whose child are you?

266
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:25,520
I don't have parents.

267
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:29,000
I'm sorry about that.

268
00:34:30,719 --> 00:34:31,920
It's okay.

269
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,920
So, would you like to wait for Thon?

270
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:41,600
No, it's fine. If he's out with friends,
he probably won't be back anytime soon.

271
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:44,679
Just tell him Phum came by.

272
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,120
Okay, Mr. Phum.

273
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:49,239
Your name sounds really cool.

274
00:34:50,280 --> 00:34:54,000
Really? No one's ever told me that before.
You're the first one.

275
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,040
Here.

276
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:01,480
I can't take it.

277
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,920
Venerable Sir taught me
never to accept money for free.

278
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:06,560
I have to work for it.

279
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:09,000
That way, I can take it.

280
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:12,360
You're such a good kid. What's your name?

281
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:14,040
My name is Kang.

282
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:16,280
That's a cute name.

283
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:20,000
I consider that working for me. Keep it.

284
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:41,240
The salad here is really good.
Try it, Mr. Thon.

285
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:50,080
Da, does Na know you're here?

286
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:53,480
Why does he need to know?

287
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:55,600
He isn't my guardian.

288
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:58,160
Why should I report everywhere I go?

289
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:06,000
Da's really friendly, Mr. Narathon.

290
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:12,280
Mook, you don't have to praise me so much
in front of Mr. Thon.

291
00:36:12,360 --> 00:36:14,400
But it's true.

292
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:18,280
Whoever gets you as a girlfriend
is seriously lucky.

293
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:21,840
I'm still happy for Na every single day

294
00:36:21,920 --> 00:36:23,720
for dating you.

295
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:30,800
Mr. Mana's your boyfriend?

296
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:31,960
Yes.

297
00:36:32,040 --> 00:36:35,480
Na and Da have been dating
for a long time.

298
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:37,720
By now,

299
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:42,000
it must be five or six years, right, Da?

300
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:57,640
What's wrong with you?

301
00:36:57,720 --> 00:37:00,680
Did you really have to drag me in here
just because you needed the bathroom?

302
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:03,000
Stop acting innocent.

303
00:37:03,080 --> 00:37:07,040
I know you intentionally told
Mr. Narathon that Na and I are dating.

304
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:11,440
Yes. Because it's true, isn't it?

305
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:17,520
Well, there's no need
to announce it to everyone like that.

306
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:22,280
I'm not the type to meddle
in other people's relationships, Da.

307
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:24,720
But the way you act
all close to Mr. Narathon

308
00:37:24,800 --> 00:37:26,920
while you already have Na,

309
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:28,880
it's inappropriate.

310
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:32,840
Stop living in the past, will you?

311
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:35,920
Having a boyfriend means
we can't talk to anyone else?

312
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:39,240
That's way too controlling.

313
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:44,160
Then if Na started
getting close to other girls,

314
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:47,120
driving them around,
taking them out to dinner,

315
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:49,560
you wouldn't get jealous at all?

316
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:54,440
I know Na would never do that.

317
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:07,040
One espresso, please.

318
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:14,400
Thon,

319
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:17,640
I just went to your house.

320
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:19,200
Why are you here, Dad?

321
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:20,640
I came to relax, obviously.

322
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:25,440
No matter what I say,
you never believe me, do you?

323
00:38:26,040 --> 00:38:28,560
I stopped trusting your words
a long time ago.

324
00:38:33,120 --> 00:38:34,520
Oh, Mr. Phum.

325
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:36,200
- Oh, Kaimook.
- Hello.

326
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:39,840
How are you here? I haven't seen you
for ages. Are you here on vacation?

327
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:42,360
Yes. My family has a vacation house here.

328
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:43,560
That's nice.

329
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:44,960
Yes.

330
00:38:46,240 --> 00:38:49,040
This is my friend, Dara.

331
00:38:49,120 --> 00:38:50,400
Hello.

332
00:38:50,480 --> 00:38:52,640
And this is Mr. Narathon.

333
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:56,080
I know him. I know him very well.

334
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:02,120
I should get going now.

335
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:04,880
Thanks for the meal.

336
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:08,280
You're welcome.

337
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:11,240
Alright.

338
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:23,400
Since when do you two know Narathon?

339
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:26,520
We only just met recently.

340
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,920
Are you staying here, Mr. Phum?

341
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:33,960
Yes. I've got some business here
for a couple of days.

342
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:36,800
If you're free,
come have dinner with me sometime.

343
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:42,440
Just give me a call beforehand, alright?
Here's my number.

344
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:45,280
Sure.

345
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:56,400
I think he definitely likes you.

346
00:39:56,480 --> 00:39:58,840
- Who?
- Mr. Phum.

347
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:02,800
Don't be ridiculous.
He's practically my dad's age.

348
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:05,080
So?

349
00:40:05,160 --> 00:40:09,440
Most importantly,
he still looks young, handsome,

350
00:40:09,520 --> 00:40:11,520
and incredibly charming.

351
00:40:12,680 --> 00:40:14,480
I saw the way he looked at you.

352
00:40:14,560 --> 00:40:17,320
If he didn't like you,
he wouldn't invite you to dinner.

353
00:40:18,680 --> 00:40:21,320
Mr. Phum probably just wants
to talk about my photos.

354
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:23,320
What photos?

355
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:27,400
He bought
every single underwater photo I took.

356
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:30,080
Exactly.

357
00:40:30,160 --> 00:40:33,240
If he didn't like you,
he'd never go that far.

358
00:40:34,120 --> 00:40:38,600
No wonder you got over Prawin so easily.

359
00:40:38,680 --> 00:40:40,240
You've already found a new target.

360
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:44,880
I'm not wishy-washy like your brother.

361
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:48,840
And remember this.
If you still want to stay friends with me,

362
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:51,120
don't bring up Prawin again.

363
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:36,760
I'm scared!

364
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:49,600
I brought you food.

365
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:53,600
I'm not scared of you anymore,
you damn ghost! Die now!

366
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,240
Uncle! Uncle!

367
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:57,800
As much as I want that piece of land,

368
00:41:57,880 --> 00:42:01,840
you trust Narathon enough to let him
do the project he's passionate about.

369
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:04,560
I don't get it, but my son gets it.
That isn't such a bad balance after all.

370
00:42:07,040 --> 00:42:09,840
What kind of motive is that?

371
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:11,320
Black coral.

372
00:42:12,080 --> 00:42:13,560
Black coral?

373
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:21,240
You're heartless!

374
00:42:58,040 --> 00:43:00,280
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
